description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a fully flexible, enthusiastic, and motivated Staff Nurse to join the team on the Derwent Ward at the Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospital. We are a 20 bedded ward devoted to elective orthopaedic surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for admitting and preparing patients for theatre ensuring that local policy is adhered to, caring for patients post-operatively and working within the MDT to ensure safe discharge of patients. the role requires a friendly and patient centred person with excellent communication skills and a commitment to maintaining and developing high standards of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Development of staff and evidence based quality care is our priority, previous Orthopaedic experience would be preferred but full training and support will be provided to the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and Poole Hospital NHS Foundation Trust merged in 2020 to form University Hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust. It is a condition of employment that all staff being recruited&lt;span&gt; will work across all sites &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: to be confirmed&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joanne Sammuller Ward Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;joanne.sammuller@rbch.nhs.uk &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0300 013 6217&lt;/p&gt;
